.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-2-15::.
The people have 6 different jobs:  chef, bartender, architect, journalist, paramedic, dressmaker
The people use 6 different means of transport: jet-ski, roller, train, trike, bike, motorbike
 1. the dressmaker is the person driving the roller##1
 2. the person driving the trike is on the right of the person driving the motorbike##1
 3. the person driving the jet-ski is between the person driving the bike and the person driving the roller##2
 4. the chef is on the far right##1
 5. the paramedic is the person driving the jet-ski##1
 6. the architect is the person driving the bike##1
 7. the journalist is the journalist##1
 8. the chef is on the right of the journalist##1
 9. the person driving the train is on the left of the person driving the motorbike##1
10. the person driving the train is on the right of the architect##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |   1    |   2    |     3     |     4      |   5    |     6     |
| Job   | dressmaker | paramedic    | architect     | bartender      | journalist    | chef |
| Transport   | roller | jet-ski | bike | train | motorbike | trike  |

