.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-2-20::.
The people use 6 different means of transport: boat, roller, van, train, taxi, car
City: prague, london, rome, nizza, hamburg, hannover
 1. the person driving the boat is on the right of the person driving the train##1
 2. the person traveling to prague is on the far left##1
 3. the person driving the taxi is on the left of the person driving the van##1
 4. the person traveling to nizza is the person driving the car##1
 5. the person driving the van is on the far right##1
 6. the person traveling to hannover is on the right of the person traveling to nizza##1
 7. the person traveling to london is the person driving the van##1
 8. the person traveling to hamburg is on the right of the person traveling to prague##1
 9. the person traveling to rome is between the person driving the car and the person driving the boat##2
10. the person driving the taxi is the person driving the taxi##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |    1    |    2    |     3      |      4      |       5       |    6    |
| Transport         | train | boat | roller | car | taxi | van |
| City   | prague | hamburg | rome      | nizza     | hannover       | london |

 